The first attempt to remove Belarus' uranium in October was particularly complicated because the material was slightly contaminated, officials say.
It was loaded onto a special train that travelled more than 1,300 miles to a Russian factory for storage and disposal, officials say.
The second attempt was decided on Monday and was carried out by plane, officials say.
The US government is paying $14 million for the effort, with much of the money going to Belarusian research with low-enriched uranium, which cannot be used for nuclear weapons.
