The James Martin Center for Nonproliferation Studies estimates that Belarus had at least 88 pounds of weapons-grade uranium this year, as well as hundreds of pounds of highly enriched uranium.
According to the joint agreement, Belarus intends to dismantle its stockpile by 2012.
Relations between Belarus and the US have been strained for years, primarily over Lukashenko's harsh disregard for human rights.
But Wednesday's statement suggests a possible rapprochement.
"Welcoming the progress of these global security issues, the United States of America and Belarus announce that increased respect for democracy and human rights in Belarus remains a central theme in improving bilateral relations, and it is essential to the progress of the country and its citizens," it says.
